OL,3,CMartyn's Law backed by more than 100
OL,4,Cbusinesses
OL,6,FMore than one hundred venues have
OL,7,Fbacked Martyn's Law to help protect
OL,8,Fthe public from terror attacks as MPs
OL,9,Fdebate the proposal in Parliament.
OL,11,FThe plans, part of the Terrorism
OL,12,F(Protection of Premises) Bill, are
OL,13,Fnamed after 29-year-old Martyn Hett,
OL,14,Fwho was murdered with 21 others in the
OL,15,F2017 Manchester Arena attack and whose
OL,16,Fmother Figen Murray has campaigned for
OL,17,Fsince.
